superintendent, overseer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inspector, who takes cognizance of, and is responsible for, the actions"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people], who is below the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray^iys","text_ar":"رَيِيس"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manager and superintendent of the affairs, who acquaints himself with the circumstances,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or a tribe, or of a company of men; of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilN","text_ar":"فَاعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAth, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"orderer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manager, of the affairs"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people, or party; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArifN","text_ar":"عَارِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) pl. as above: (S, IAth, Msb:) it is said that he is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over a few persons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manokib","text_ar":"مَنْكِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is over five"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuraqaA='","text_ar":"عُرَقَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", then the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amiyr","text_ar":"اَمِير"},{"kind":"text","text":"is over these. (Msb.) It is said in a trad. that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurafaA='","text_ar":"عُرَفَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"are in Hell, as a caution against undertaking the office of chief, or head, on account of the trial that is therein; for when one does not perform the duty thereof, he sins, and deserves punishment. (TA.) ―         -b3-  [It is now used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A monitor in a school, who hears the lessons of the other scholars."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoruwfN","text_ar":"مَعْرُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with which it is syn."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","K","TA","S","O","IAth","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}